==English==
===Etymology===
From colloquial Arabic {{ARchar|[[عالمة]]}} (‘ālima) ‘singer’, originally a feminine adjective meaning ‘learned, knowledgeable’, from {{ARchar|[[علم]]}} (‘alima) ‘to know’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈælmə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''almah'''|'''[[almahs]]''' or '''almah'''}}
# an Egyptian singer or dancing-girl used for entertainment or as a professional mourner

